===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|thaugh}}, {{m|enm|thagh|}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|þēah||though, although, even if, that, however, nevertheless, yet, still; whether}}, later superseded in many dialects by {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|though}}, {{m|enm|thogh}}, from {{etyl|non|en}} {{m|non|*þóh}} (later {{m|non|þó}}); both from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*þauh||though}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*to-}}, suffixed with {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*-hw}} &lt; {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*-kʷe||and}}. Akin to Scots {{m|sco|thoch||though}}, {{cog|stq|dach||though}}, {{cog|fy|dôch}}, {{m|fy|dochs||though}}, {{cog|nl|doch||though}}, {{cog|de|doch||though}}, {{cog|sv|dock||however, still}}, {{cog|is|þó||though}}. More at [[that]].

